      "content": "I can see that the problem is that we're trying to calculate the sum of products of pairs of numbers from 0 to n-1, where the product is taken modulo 123. \n\nWe can calculate this sum in O(1) time by using the properties of modular arithmetic. \n\nThe sum of products of pairs of numbers from 0 to n-1 can be calculated as follows:\n\n```python\ndef heavy_sum(n):\n    mod = 123\n    total = 0\n    for i in range(1, n + 1):\n        total += i * (n * (n - 1) // 2 - i) % mod\n    return total\n```\n\nThis solution works because the sum of products of pairs of numbers from 0 to n-1 is equal to the sum of products of pairs of numbers from 0 to n-1, where we fix the first number to be i and the second number to be n-i. \n\nThis solution has a time complexity of O(n), but it's much faster than the original solution because it avoids the nested loops.",
